    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-11-14T16:45:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-11-14T16:45:00-05:00" n="1394"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1394">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.51/1038</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Jefferson</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-11-14T16:00:00-05:45">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 14, 1917, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Both Houses of Congress have approved the contracts as received in their original
                    form and all amendments were withdrawn.</p>
                <p>In view of above, and referring to the Department’s November 2, 4 p.m., I request
                    that the Department immediately approve the payment of the balance one hundred
                    and fifty-five thousand dollars to be used in payment of pressing indebtedness
                    budget deficit 1917 and back salaries.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Jefferson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
